  <div>
  <h1>Beshan ka Halwa recipe</h1>
</div>
<selector class="icon">
  <div  class="quick">
  <p><h2>Beshan ka halwa is a indian desert <span style="color:blue;">made </span>with gram flour, sugar, ghee, and nuts.
    I like to eat <span style="color:green;">sweet </span>dish because it's very tasty.
    It can be eaten as a after meal<span style="text-decoration:underline;"> dessert</span>.</h2>
  </p>
</div>
</selector>
  <p>
  <img src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vegrecipesofindia.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/besan-halwa-1a.jpg" alt="error" />
  </p>
    <!-- Unordered List -->
  <strong><h1>Ingredients</strong></h1>
  <ul class="heart">
    <li>1 cup besan or gram flour</li>
    <li>1/2 cup Ghee</li>
    <li>1/2 to 3/4 cup sugar (use as needed, i used 3/4)</li>
    <li>2 cup milk or water (or 1 cup milk 1 cup water)</li>
    <li>1/3 tsp cardamom pouder or elachi pouder</li>
    <li>2 tsp almonds or badam sliced</li>
    <li>2 tsp pistachios sliced</li>
  </ul>
  <!-- Ordered List -->
  <strong><h1>Preparation for besan ka halwa</strong></h1>
  <ol class="special">
    <li>Pour water, milk and sugar to a pot and disslove the sugar completly.
      Bring it to a boil ğŸ¥›.</li>
    <li>On another burner, heat ghee in a heavy  bottom pan ğŸ³.</li>
    <li>Add besan and begain to roast on a medium flame stirring contionuously
    untill aromatic and deep golden.</li>
    <li>When the besan is about to be done, reduce the flame to low ğŸ”¥.</li>
  </ol>
  <strong><h1>Making besan ka halwa</strong></h1>
  <ol class="special">
    <li>Quickly and slowly pour the milk in small quantities to the
      besan stirring continuously ğŸ‘.</li>
    <li>Keep stirring continuously breaking the lumps and cooking.</li>
    <li>When the moisture is absorded, add 1 tsp ghee and stir. Within few 
      minutes the halwa will begain to leave the slide of the pen.</li>
    <li>Cook for another 2 to 3 minutes untill the ghee begains to release.
    Remove to serving bowls ğŸ½ï¸.</li>
    <li>Sprinkle sliced almonds & pistas. Serve besan ka halwa warm or hot ğŸ˜‹.</li>
  </ol>
